Russians have been warned about fake calls from banks
In Russia, the number of calls from fraudsters who change the phone number of the bank has increased.
This is reported by Kommersant with reference to the data of the Central Bank.
In the summer of 2019, the regulator transmitted information to communication operators about more than 2,500 numbers from which customers of various financial organizations were called.
In 189 cases, the operators found a substitution of the number.
Another 218 numbers were blocked, and in 59 cases a restriction on the use of financial services was imposed.
Deputy head of the information security department of the Central Bank, Artem Sychev, said that a wide range of Russian banks faced a number change.
He explained that the operators do not always respond to the Central Bank’s warnings about fraudulent calls, citing the absence of such an obligation in the Law on Communication.
In the bank "Otkrytie", Rosbank and Alfa-bank confirmed the information about the increase in the number of fraudulent calls with a change of number.
As reported in the press service "Beeline", part of the information about fraudulent calls that the Central Bank transmitted was incorrect: the lists included numbers that are really used by banks to communicate with customers.
Blocking them would lead to failures in the work of the organization.
Artem Sychev said that the Central Bank plans to create a database of fraudsters' numbers, to which the communications operator will be contacted every time the number is checked.
He explained that the creation of such a basis would require amendments to the legislation.
